import{_ as n,c as o,j as e,a as i,G as r,a2 as s,B as l,o as c}from"./chunks/framework.CdbxnhrM.js";const y=JSON.parse(`{"title":"🧑‍🏫 Constitutional Amendment","description":"A constitutional amendment refers to the process of revising or supplementing the constitution to modify the nation's governance structure and power dynamics. It is an essential procedure to maintain constitutional order while adapting to changing societal and historical demands.","frontmatter":{"description":"A constitutional amendment refers to the process of revising or supplementing the constitution to modify the nation's governance structure and power dynamics. It is an essential procedure to maintain constitutional order while adapting to changing societal and historical demands.","head":[["meta",{"property":"og:title","content":"Constitutional Amendment"}],["meta",{"property":"og:description","content":"A constitutional amendment refers to the process of revising or supplementing the constitution to modify the nation's governance structure and power dynamics. It is an essential procedure to maintain constitutional order while adapting to changing societal and historical demands."}],["meta",{"property":"og:image","content":"/images/quant-haun.svg"}],["meta",{"property":"og:url","content":"https://quant-haunblog.github.io/en/feed/social/constitutional-amendment"}]]},"headers":[],"relativePath":"en/feed/social/constitutional-amendment.md","filePath":"en/feed/social/constitutional-amendment.md","lastUpdated":null}`),d={name:"en/feed/social/constitutional-amendment.md"};function m(u,t,h,p,f,g){const a=l("AdsInarticle");return c(),o("div",null,[t[0]||(t[0]=e("h1",{id:"🧑‍🏫-constitutional-amendment",tabindex:"-1"},[i("🧑‍🏫 Constitutional Amendment "),e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#🧑‍🏫-constitutional-amendment","aria-label":'Permalink to "🧑‍🏫 Constitutional Amendment"'},"​")],-1)),t[1]||(t[1]=e("p",null,"Today's Social Headlines | 2024.12.25",-1)),t[2]||(t[2]=e("h2",{id:"📌-reigniting-the-debate-on-constitutional-amendment-the-need-for-a-presidential-system-reform-and-power-decentralization",tabindex:"-1"},[i("📌 Reigniting the Debate on Constitutional Amendment - The Need for a Presidential System Reform and Power Decentralization "),e("a",{class:"header-anchor",href:"#📌-reigniting-the-debate-on-constitutional-amendment-the-need-for-a-presidential-system-reform-and-power-decentralization","aria-label":'Permalink to "📌 Reigniting the Debate on Constitutional Amendment - The Need for a Presidential System Reform and Power Decentralization"'},"​")],-1)),t[3]||(t[3]=e("p",null,"In the wake of the martial law declaration, the political arena has reignited discussions on amending the constitution to address the shortcomings of the current presidential system. The need for constitutional changes, focusing on reducing presidential authority and introducing a four-year term with the possibility of reelection, has been raised by both the ruling and opposition parties, making it a key political issue.",-1)),t[4]||(t[4]=e("p",null,"However, skepticism remains regarding the feasibility of a substantive constitutional amendment due to past failures and the ongoing political polarization.",-1)),r(a),t[5]||(t[5]=s('<h2 id="_1️⃣-definition" tabindex="-1">1️⃣ Definition <a class="header-anchor" href="#_1️⃣-definition" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;1️⃣ Definition&quot;">​</a></h2><p>A constitutional amendment refers to the process of revising or supplementing the constitution to modify the nation&#39;s governance structure and power dynamics. It is an essential procedure to maintain constitutional order while adapting to changing societal and historical demands.</p><p>In particular, constitutional amendments are often required to address pressing political and social issues or to create a fairer power structure. It is not merely a matter of institutional reform but a significant act of collaboration between the people and the legislature to set a new direction for the nation.</p><h2 id="_2️⃣-principles-and-legal-framework" tabindex="-1">2️⃣ Principles and Legal Framework <a class="header-anchor" href="#_2️⃣-principles-and-legal-framework" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;2️⃣ Principles and Legal Framework&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="📖-articles-128–130-of-the-constitution" tabindex="-1">📖 Articles 128–130 of the Constitution <a class="header-anchor" href="#📖-articles-128–130-of-the-constitution" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;📖 Articles 128–130 of the Constitution&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li><strong>Initiation</strong>: A constitutional amendment is initiated by the president or by a majority of sitting members of the National Assembly.</li><li><strong>Parliamentary Approval</strong>: It must be approved by at least two-thirds of the total members of the National Assembly.</li><li><strong>Final Approval</strong>: The amendment is finalized through a national referendum.</li></ul><h3 id="📖-policy-background" tabindex="-1">📖 Policy Background <a class="header-anchor" href="#📖-policy-background" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;📖 Policy Background&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>Since the 1987 amendment, the current constitution has remained in effect, playing a vital role in democratization. However, it has also exposed the limitations of the winner-takes-all presidential system.</li></ul><h3 id="📖-historical-cases" tabindex="-1">📖 Historical Cases <a class="header-anchor" href="#📖-historical-cases" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;📖 Historical Cases&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>The 1987 amendment ended military dictatorship and enabled democratic transitions of power.</li><li>However, subsequent discussions about transitioning to a parliamentary system were repeatedly derailed due to political disagreements.</li></ul><h3 id="📖-contemporary-discussions" tabindex="-1">📖 Contemporary Discussions <a class="header-anchor" href="#📖-contemporary-discussions" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;📖 Contemporary Discussions&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>A four-year term with reelection could strengthen the midterm evaluation of governments and expand citizens&#39; voting rights.</li><li>The proposal aims to prevent authoritarian tendencies by decentralizing presidential power.</li></ul><h2 id="_3️⃣-impacts" tabindex="-1">3️⃣ Impacts <a class="header-anchor" href="#_3️⃣-impacts" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;3️⃣ Impacts&quot;">​</a></h2><p>A constitutional amendment fundamentally reshapes the foundation of national governance, with profound political, economic, and social implications.</p><h3 id="💡-political-impacts" tabindex="-1">💡 Political Impacts <a class="header-anchor" href="#💡-political-impacts" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;💡 Political Impacts&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>A constitutional amendment could enhance power-sharing and cooperative governance, thereby securing political stability. If a balanced distribution of power is achieved, it may shift the political culture toward consensus rather than conflict.</li></ul><h3 id="💡-economic-impacts" tabindex="-1">💡 Economic Impacts <a class="header-anchor" href="#💡-economic-impacts" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;💡 Economic Impacts&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>It could strengthen domestic and international market confidence by ensuring stable policy implementation. Moreover, it provides a structural basis to support sustainable, long-term economic policies.</li></ul><h3 id="💡-social-impacts" tabindex="-1">💡 Social Impacts <a class="header-anchor" href="#💡-social-impacts" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;💡 Social Impacts&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>Expanding citizen participation in decision-making processes could fortify democratic governance. However, hasty or inadequately discussed amendments might lead to power vacuums or political instability.</li></ul><h2 id="_4️⃣-comparison-with-related-terms" tabindex="-1">4️⃣ Comparison with Related Terms <a class="header-anchor" href="#_4️⃣-comparison-with-related-terms" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;4️⃣ Comparison with Related Terms&quot;">​</a></h2><h3 id="🔎-constitutional-revision" tabindex="-1">🔎 Constitutional Revision <a class="header-anchor" href="#🔎-constitutional-revision" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;🔎 Constitutional Revision&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>This refers to modifying or adding specific provisions of the constitution, aiming for limited changes. Current discussions in South Korea fall under this category.</li></ul><h3 id="🔎-constitutional-transition" tabindex="-1">🔎 Constitutional Transition <a class="header-anchor" href="#🔎-constitutional-transition" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;🔎 Constitutional Transition&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>This involves adopting an entirely new constitution, typically associated with revolutionary or extreme systemic changes.</li></ul><h3 id="🔎-political-reform" tabindex="-1">🔎 Political Reform <a class="header-anchor" href="#🔎-political-reform" aria-label="Permalink to &quot;🔎 Political Reform&quot;">​</a></h3><ul><li>Unlike constitutional amendments, political reform focuses on improving governance structures through legal or policy changes, often requiring less drastic measures.</li></ul>',27))])}const v=n(d,[["render",m]]);export{y as __pageData,v as default};
